SUMMARY:
The frontend type definitions, filter UI, and row rendering code are all built around a 3-value status contract (pending, approved, rejected) that does not exist in the backend. The backend returns items (not deposits), uses field name coin (not currency), and emits 6 statuses
— none of which include approved. Every non-pending/rejected deposit will render broken.

FILES:
- path: /algonney/BRIDGE/frontend/front/src/components/adminv2/types/index.ts
- function: DepositStatus, AdminDeposit, AdminDepositsResponse
- path: /algonney/BRIDGE/frontend/front/src/components/adminv2/sections/DepositsSection.tsx
- function: DepositsSectionInner

FLOW:
1. AdminDepositsResponse typed as { deposits: AdminDeposit[]; ... } — hook reads data?.deposits
2. Backend responds with { items: [...], total, has_more } — deposits key is absent → data?.deposits is undefined → table renders 0 rows
3. For any rows that do render, row.currency is accessed (line 92) — backend sends coin → renders undefined (blank)
4. Status badge calls statusVariantMap[value as DepositStatus] (line 125) — backend sends credited, confirmed, below_minimum, manual_review — none are keys in the map → variant is undefined → StatusBadge renders with no variant
5. Status filter dropdown (lines 277–286) offers approved as a query param option — backend does not recognize approved → returns 0 results when that filter is active

FINDINGS:

Finding 1 — Response key mismatch (root cause of missing records):
// types/index.ts line 58-63
export interface AdminDepositsResponse {
deposits: AdminDeposit[]; // ← frontend expects "deposits"
total: number;
page: number;
page_size: number;
}
// Backend actually returns: { items: [...], total, has_more }
// "deposits" key does not exist on the response → undefined → 0 rows rendered

Finding 2 — DepositStatus union is missing 4 backend values:
// types/index.ts line 41
export type DepositStatus = 'pending' | 'approved' | 'rejected';
// Backend contract: pending | confirmed | credited | rejected | below_minimum | manual_review
// Missing: confirmed, credited, below_minimum, manual_review
// Phantom: 'approved' — backend never emits this value

Finding 3 — statusVariantMap has phantom key, missing 4 real keys:
// DepositsSection.tsx lines 17-21
const statusVariantMap: Record<DepositStatus, 'success' | 'warning' | 'danger'> = {
pending: 'warning',
approved: 'success', // ← ghost: backend never sends 'approved'
rejected: 'danger',
// missing: confirmed, credited, below_minimum, manual_review
};
// Line 125: statusVariantMap[value as DepositStatus] → undefined for 4 real statuses

Finding 4 — currency field vs coin field:
// AdminDeposit interface line 48
currency: string; // ← frontend field name
// Backend returns: coin: "USDT" (field is named "coin", not "currency")

// DepositsSection.tsx line 92
{row.currency} // ← accesses .currency → undefined → renders blank
// DepositsSection.tsx line 96-100
accessorKey: 'currency' // ← column reads .currency → undefined → blank column

Finding 5 — filter UI sends invalid status to backend:
// DepositsSection.tsx lines 277-286
<option value="approved">Approved</option> // ← sends ?status=approved to API
// Backend DepositTransactionStatus enum has no 'approved' value
// → backend returns 0 results when this filter is selected

Finding 6 — AdminDepositsResponse pagination shape mismatch:
// Frontend expects: { deposits, total, page, page_size }
// Backend returns: { items, total, has_more }
// 'page' and 'page_size' are absent from backend response
// 'has_more' is absent from frontend type

LIKELY_BREAKPOINTS:
- types/index.ts line 58: deposits: key — should be items:
- types/index.ts line 41: DepositStatus union — missing 4 values, has 1 phantom
- types/index.ts line 48: currency: field — should be coin:
- DepositsSection.tsx lines 17–21: statusVariantMap — missing 4 entries
- DepositsSection.tsx line 92: {row.currency} — will render blank
- DepositsSection.tsx line 96: accessorKey: 'currency' — maps to undefined
- DepositsSection.tsx lines 277–286: <option value="approved"> — invalid backend status
- Hook access of data?.deposits — returns undefined because backend sends items

RECOMMENDED_NEXT_CHECK:
- Read useAdminDeposits.ts in full to confirm whether it accesses data?.deposits or data?.items — this is the exact line causing zero rows, and confirms whether the fix is in the hook or the type definition
